Abstract = {This paper introduces the pedagogic model of the OIKODOMOS Virtual
   Campus, a pedagogic research project developed over the last two years
   by a consortium of four Schools of Architecture and Urban Planning and
   two educational technology groups. The pedagogic model developed for
   this project derives from the design studio teaching that constitutes
   the backbone of design education. It is based on the collaborative
   design and implementation of blended on-line and on-site learning
   activities. A technological platform has been created specifically to
   support the learning model developed for the project. Learning Outcomes
   have been collaboratively designed by participating schools to
   facilitate the evaluation of student works.},
